From: Ian Rogers <irogers@google.com>
Date: Tue, 27 May 2025 20:26:32 -0700
Subject: perf test demangle-java: Don't segv if demangling fails
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: 07f2b1287c970e0706c0e8fbb358ca4c1e7f8d4e
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc1
References: perf-sle16.1-v6.19-userspace-update

The buffer returned by dso__demangle_sym() may be NULL, don't segv in
strcmp if this happens.

Currently this happens for NO_LIBELF=1 builds.

